<div class="c260_2">
<div id="v260.2.1"><span class="H2261 s">I <i>am</i> the rose</span><span class="H8289 s"> of Sharon</span><span class="H7799 s">, <i>and</i> the lily</span><span class="H6010 s"> of the valleys</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.2"><span class="H7799 s">As the lily</span><span class="H2336 s"> among thorns</span><span class="H7474 s">, so <i>is</i> my love</span><span class="H1323 s"> among the daughters</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.3"><span class="H8598 s">As the apple tree</span><span class="H6086 s"> among the trees</span><span class="H3293 s"> of the wood</span><span class="H1730 s">, so <i>is</i> my beloved</span><span class="H1121 s"> among the sons</span><span class="H3427 s">. I sat</span><span class="H6738 s"> down under his shadow</span><span class="H2530 s"> with great delight</span><span class="H6529 s">, and his fruit</span><span class="H4966 s"> <i>was</i> sweet</span><span class="H2441 s"> to my taste</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (I sat…: Heb. I delighted and sat down, etc) (taste: Heb. palate)</span></div>
<div id="v260.2.4"><span class="H935 s">He brought</span><span class="H3196 s"> me to the banqueting</span><span class="H1004 s"> house</span><span class="H1714 s">, and his banner</span><span class="H160 s"> over me <i>was</i> love</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (banqueting…: Heb. house of wine)</span></div>
<div id="v260.2.5"><span class="H5564 s">Stay</span><span class="H809 s"> me with flagons</span><span class="H7502 s">, comfort</span><span class="H8598 s"> me with apples</span><span class="H2470 s">: for I <i>am</i> sick</span><span class="H160 s"> of love</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (comfort…: Heb. straw me with apples)</span></div>
<div id="v260.2.6"><span class="H8040 s">His left hand</span><span class="H7218 s"> <i>is</i> under my head</span><span class="H3225 s">, and his right hand</span><span class="H2263 s"> doth embrace</span> me.</div>
<div id="v260.2.7"><span class="H7650 s">I charge</span><span class="H1323 s"> you, O ye daughters</span><span class="H3389 s"> of Jerusalem</span><span class="H6643 s">, by the roes</span><span class="H176 s">, and</span><span class="H355 s"> by the hinds</span><span class="H7704 s"> of the field</span><span class="H5782 s">, that ye stir not up</span><span class="H5782 s">, nor awake</span><span class="H160 s"> <i>my</i> love</span><span class="H2654 s">, till he please</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (I charge…: Heb. I adjure you)</span></div>
<div id="v260.2.8"><span class="H6963 s">The voice</span><span class="H1730 s"> of my beloved</span><span class="H935 s">! behold, he cometh</span><span class="H1801 s"> leaping</span><span class="H2022 s"> upon the mountains</span><span class="H7092 s">, skipping</span><span class="H1389 s"> upon the hills</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.9"><span class="H1730 s">My beloved</span><span class="H1819 s"> is like</span><span class="H6643 s"> a roe</span><span class="H6082 s"> or a young</span><span class="H354 s"> hart</span><span class="H5975 s">: behold, he standeth</span><span class="H310 s"> behind</span><span class="H3796 s"> our wall</span><span class="H7688 s">, he looketh forth</span><span class="H2474 s"> at the windows</span><span class="H6692 s">, shewing</span><span class="H2762 s"> himself through the lattice</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (shewing…: Heb. flourishing)</span></div>
<div id="v260.2.10"><span class="H1730 s">My beloved</span><span class="H6030 s"> spake</span><span class="H559 s">, and said</span><span class="H6965 s"> unto me, Rise up</span><span class="H7474 s">, my love</span><span class="H3303 s">, my fair one</span><span class="H3212 s">, and come away</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.11"><span class="H5638 s">For, lo, the winter</span><span class="H5674 s"> is past</span><span class="H1653 s">, the rain</span><span class="H2498 s"> is over</span><span class="H1980 s"> <i>and</i> gone</span>;</div>
<div id="v260.2.12"><span class="H5339 s">The flowers</span><span class="H7200 s"> appear</span><span class="H776 s"> on the earth</span><span class="H6256 s">; the time</span><span class="H2158 s"> of the singing</span><span class="H5060 s"> <i>of birds</i> is come</span><span class="H6963 s">, and the voice</span><span class="H8449 s"> of the turtle</span><span class="H8085 s"> is heard</span><span class="H776 s"> in our land</span>;</div>
<div id="v260.2.13"><span class="H8384 s">The fig tree</span><span class="H2590 s"> putteth forth</span><span class="H6291 s"> her green figs</span><span class="H1612 s">, and the vines</span><span class="H5563 s"> <i>with</i> the tender grape</span><span class="H5414 s"> give</span><span class="H7381 s"> a <i>good</i> smell</span><span class="H6965 s">. Arise</span><span class="H7474 s">, my love</span><span class="H3303 s">, my fair one</span><span class="H3212 s">, and come away</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.14"><span class="H3123 s">O my dove</span><span class="H2288 s">, <i>that art</i> in the clefts</span><span class="H5553 s"> of the rock</span><span class="H5643 s">, in the secret</span><span class="H4095 s"> <i>places</i> of the stairs</span><span class="H7200 s">, let me see</span><span class="H4758 s"> thy countenance</span><span class="H8085 s">, let me hear</span><span class="H6963 s"> thy voice</span><span class="H6156 s">; for sweet</span><span class="H6963 s"> <i>is</i> thy voice</span><span class="H4758 s">, and thy countenance</span><span class="H5000 s"> <i>is</i> comely</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.15"><span class="H270 s">Take</span><span class="H7776 s"> us the foxes</span><span class="H6996 s">, the little</span><span class="H7776 s"> foxes</span><span class="H2254 s">, that spoil</span><span class="H3754 s"> the vines</span><span class="H3754 s">: for our vines</span><span class="H5563 s"> <i>have</i> tender grapes</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.16"><span class="H1730 s">My beloved</span><span class="H7462 s"> <i>is</i> mine, and I <i>am</i> his: he feedeth</span><span class="H7799 s"> among the lilies</span>.</div>
<div id="v260.2.17"><span class="H3117 s">Until the day</span><span class="H6315 s"> break</span><span class="H6752 s">, and the shadows</span><span class="H5127 s"> flee away</span><span class="H5437 s">, turn</span><span class="H1730 s">, my beloved</span><span class="H1819 s">, and be thou like</span><span class="H6643 s"> a roe</span><span class="H6082 s"> or a young</span><span class="H354 s"> hart</span><span class="H2022 s"> upon the mountains</span><span class="H1336 s"> of Bether</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (of Bether: or, of division)</span></div></div>
